  "doc_id": "47579",
  "text": "There are several MATLAB based tools for analyzing properties of switched systems using simulations. Breach [CITATION_1] uses sensitivity analysis for analyzing STL properties of systems using simulations. This analysis is sound and relatively complete for linear systems, but does not provide formal guarantees for nonlinear systems. S-Taliro [CITATION_2] is a falsification engine that search for counterexamples using Monte-Carlo techniques and hence provides only probabilistic guarantees. STRONG [CITATION_3] uses robustness analysis for coverage of all executions from a given initial set by constructing bisimulation functions. Currently this tool computes bisimulation functions for only linear or affine hybrid systems and does not handle nonlinear systems.",
